<paragraph blockId="8.[151,871,655,681]" box="[151,871,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,871,655,681]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,871,655,681]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName authority="Ferro &amp; Jach, 2000" authorityName="Ferro &amp; Jach" authorityYear="2000" box="[151,631,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachthi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,381,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Hydraena arachthi</emphasis>
Ferro &amp; Jäch, 
<quantity box="[572,631,655,681]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" unit="in" value="2000.0">2000</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in the Peloponnese
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,726,966]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName box="[151,282,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachthi">
<emphasis box="[151,282,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">H. arachthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of a single male collected in 
<quantity box="[941,1028,726,750]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05714" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" unit="in" value="1991.0">1991 in</quantity>
the Arachthos River, on the border between Arta and Ioannina districts, Ipiros province, western 
<collectingCountry box="[844,927,762,786]" name="Greece" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Greece</collectingCountry>
. The species was so far only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[151,252,798,822]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
, and is apparently closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Jach, 1988" authorityName="Jach" authorityYear="1988" box="[690,1095,798,822]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cappadocica">
<emphasis box="[690,957,798,822]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Hydraena cappadocica</emphasis>
Jäch, 
<number box="[1036,1095,798,822]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</taxonomicName>
. A single teneral male of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachthi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">H. arachthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in marginal gravels on 
<date box="[629,749,834,858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="2012-06-26">
<number box="[629,656,834,858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" value="26.0">26</number>
/vi/ 
<quantity box="[693,749,834,858]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11048" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" unit="in" value="2012.0">2012</quantity>
</date>
in the Alphios River nr. Archaea Olympia, this being the first record from the Peloponnese, and a significant range extension for this apparently rare species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Orchymont" authorityName="Orchymont" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simonidea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Hydraena simonidea</emphasis>
Orchymont
</taxonomicName>
was found with 
<taxonomicName box="[613,748,907,931]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arachthi">
<emphasis box="[613,748,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">H. arachthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Alphios, together with numerous 
<taxonomicName box="[1237,1343,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis box="[1237,1343,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">H. morio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subjuncta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">H. subjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
